git

permanent record
time machine

timeline...
----o-----o-----o-----o----o----o------o
    * -each of these is a "commit"

repositories are a permanent record, time machine
	local: on your own machine
	remote: on github or other similar service (ie Dropbox)


parallel universes:
----o-----o-----o-----o----o----o------o
       |   |___o______Ryan____o|  |
       |______o__Ben______o_______|

merge conflict: prompts selection of which changes to save

*starting a reps*
	create a new remote repo at http://github.com/new
	create a new local repo in the local folder
		- cd ~/vagant-lamp/sites/codeup.dev/
		- git init
		- git add filename.html file2.cssie css/site.css
			- git add .
			- git add -A  "adds all the things"
		- git commit
		- git status at any time
		- git remote add origin <remote repo addy> (tells local repository where we're sending the files)
		- git push -u origin master


*working in an existing repo*
	- add and modify files
	- cd to codeup.dev
	- git status at any time
	- git add filename.html or git add -A
	- git commit
	- git push origin master -  recommend at least a couple times a day; when you finish something or leave the work


